replies.body:
> [{quoted}](name=Raxistaicho,realm=NA,application-id=3ErqAdtq,discussion-id=8MUruWrk,comment-id=00040002,timestamp=2017-05-07T04:01:53.970+0000)
>
> What you guys probably should do is make a basic item that provides cdr. That way it could build into the other two and not feel weird providing a stat not given by any of their components.

There's no cdr base item (except {{item:3301}} ) because cdr is powerful and it's important to limit how available it is in the early game.

Most cdr components come from two of the base item: {{item:3114}} {{item:3067}} {{item:3133}} {{item:3101}}

A few are from upgrading the base item: {{item:3108}} {{item:3057}} 

And one outlier: {{item:3024}} 

---

If the items in the OP all want to keep their cdr, probably the easiest way to do it is make all those items build from {{item:3067}} , then replace {{item:3211}} w/ some combination of {{item:1033}} {{item:1057}} {{item:1028}}

---

An alternative would be to make {{item:3211}}  to build from {{item:1033}} + {{item:1033}} , to mirror {{item:3082}}
In this case, the build path would probably be something like {{item:3211}} +{{item:3067}} +{{item:1028}}  = {{item:3065}} 

---

A third option would be to shift things around so {{item:3211}} itself gives cdr (it would probably need to lose the hp regen passive, or else it would have to be too expensive).
